# m5_grapple_ceiling.shot — exercises the grapple/swing flow on a
# purpose-built map (assets/maps/grapple_test.lvl) with a ceiling and
# three grapple targets at different heights, so the swing physics
# gets an environment the tutorial map can't provide.
#
# The .lvl is built by tools/editor/shots/grapple_test_map.shot —
# run that FIRST. Layout:
#   - 60×30 tiles = 1920×960 px world
#   - Ceiling: y=0..64 (full width, grappable)
#   - Floor:   y=896..960
#   - Walls:   x=0..32, x=1888..1920
#   - Beam   B: 600..900,  y=300..332     (mid-air horizontal beam)
#   - Pillar C: 1300..1332, y=64..500     (hangs from ceiling)
#   - Pillar D: 1700..1732, y=500..896    (floor-rooted)
#
# What this verifies (read the .log for SHOT_LOG transitions):
#   1. Ceiling grapple from mid-air → swing → retract.
#      With MIN_REST_LEN=100 the head should stay clear of the
#      ceiling tile boundary (this is the "stuck in the ceiling"
#      regression the user reported).
#   2. Disconnect, fall to floor, walk under beam B, grapple it,
#      swing.
#   3. Chain re-fire mid-swing onto pillar C (BTN_FIRE while
#      ATTACHED auto-releases + fires a new head).
#   4. Final disconnect.

window 1280 720
seed 7 7
out build/shots/m5_grapple_ceiling
loadout - "Pulse Rifle" "Grappling Hook" Light Standard
load_lvl assets/maps/grapple_test.lvl

# Spawn mid-air below the ceiling so the first beat is a clean
# straight-up grapple.
spawn_at 400 200
contact_sheet sheet cols 4 cell 480 270

# ---- Beat 1: ceiling grapple + retract -----------------------------
# Mech is in free-fall from spawn. Swap to grapple, fire straight up
# at the ceiling. Distance ~150 px, well within range.
at  10 shot t010_falling
at  15 tap swap
at  20 shot t020_secondary

at  22 aim 400 40              # straight up into the ceiling
at  25 tap fire
at  40 shot t040_attached_ceiling

# Hold W to retract toward the ceiling. Mech zip-lines up. With
# MIN_REST_LEN=100 the head should sit ~40 px below the ceiling
# tile boundary (anchor at y≈68 + min rest 100 = pelvis y≈168;
# head ~120; head_top ~112; ceiling extends to y=64). 48 px
# clearance at min retract.
at  45 press jet
at  90 shot t090_retracting
at  95 release jet
at 110 shot t110_after_retract

# Disconnect.
at 140 tap use
at 160 shot t160_after_release

# ---- Beat 2: walk right + grapple Beam B (mid-air) -----------------
# Wait for the mech to land + run east to under the beam (x=750).
# RUN_SPEED_PXS = 280 → 60 ticks of run = 280 px → from ~400 to ~680.
# We hold a bit longer to clear the beam's leading edge.
at 200 press right
at 280 release right
at 290 shot t290_under_beam

at 295 aim 750 320             # beam B
at 300 tap fire
at 350 shot t350_beam_attached
at 400 shot t400_beam_swing

# ---- Beat 3: chain re-fire mid-swing onto Pillar C -----------------
# Cooldown is 1.20 s = 72 ticks; last fire at t=300, eligible at
# t=372. Aim toward pillar C and re-fire.
at 380 aim 1300 480            # pillar C, near the bottom of the hang
at 385 tap fire                # chain re-fire (release + new fire)
at 430 shot t430_pillar_attached
at 480 shot t480_pillar_swing

# ---- Beat 4: final release -----------------------------------------
at 520 tap use
at 540 shot t540_final_released

at 600 end
